}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Formats a size (for example the size of a file) into a human
readable string. Sizes are rounded to the nearest size prefix
(KB, MB, GB) and are displayed rounded to the nearest tenth.
E.g. the file size 3292528 bytes will be converted into the
string "3.1 MB".</p>  <p>The prefix units base is 1024 (i.e. 1 KB is 1024 bytes).</p>  <p>This string should be freed with <link xref="GLib.free"/> when not needed any longer.</p>
  <p>Since 2.16</p>
